344  /* @brief Construct a planner termination condition, by default a simple time limit
345  @param timeout The maximum time (in seconds) that can be used for planning
346  @param start The point in time from which planning is considered to have started
347 
348  An additional planner termination condition can be specified per planner
349  configuration in ompl_planning.yaml via the `termination_condition` parameter.
350  Possible values are:
351 
352  * `Iteration[num]`: Terminate after `num` iterations. Here, `num` should be replaced
353  with a positive integer.
354  * `CostConvergence[solutions_window,epsilon]`: Terminate after the cost (as specified
355  by an optimization objective) has converged. The parameter `solutions_window`
356  specifies the minimum number of solutions to use in deciding whether a planner has
357  converged. The parameter `epsilon` is the threshold to consider for convergence.
358  This should be a positive number close to 0. If the cumulative moving average does
359  not change by a relative fraction of epsilon after a new better solution is found,
360  convergence has been reached.
361  * `ExactSolution`: Terminate as soon as an exact solution is found or a timeout
362  occurs. This modifies the behavior of anytime/optimizing planners to terminate
363  upon discovering the first feasible solution.
364 
365  In all cases, the planner will terminate when either the user-specified termination
366  condition is satisfied or the time limit specified by `timeout` has been reached,
367  whichever occurs first.
368  */
369  virtual ob::PlannerTerminationCondition constructPlannerTerminationCondition(double timeout,
370  const ompl::time::point& start);
371
